result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin John Frye was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Austin John Frye is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Austin John Frye was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Megan E. Kelly   DF ATTY:  Joseph R. Caton   DF:  Austin John Frye appeared. Case called at 11:44 a.m. Atty Caton states there is an agreement and recites agreement.Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NC to Ct 2in 15CM570 . DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 2 Possession of Drug Paraphernalia in 15CM570. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 1 in 15CM570. Sentencing arguments. Appeal must be filed within 20 days. Crt orders:

- $500 fine inclusive of costs. BOND TO APPLY. 

- DNA Sample

- Court states defendant can apply for expungement upon payment of fines and submitting a DNA Sample
